                 <p class="text-center mb-4" id="sweatchloride-text">Sweat chloride concentration serves as a direct biomarker of CFTR protein function. The therapy significantly reduced sweat chloride levels, bringing them closer to the non-CF diagnostic range, indicating improved channel activity.</p>
